'''Fergus Gordon Anckorn''' (10 December 1918 – 22 March 2018)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://fepowhistory.com/2018/03/23/fergus-anckorn-the-conjuror-on-the-kwai/|title=Fergus Anckorn: The Conjuror on the Kwai|author=|date=23 March 2018|website=fepowhistory.com|accessdate=10 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-5540581/Japanese-Prisoner-War-known-Conjuror-River-Kwai-dies-aged-99.html|title=Japanese PoW camp survivor who inspired BGT magician dies aged 99|author=|date=|website=dailymail.co.uk|accessdate=10 April 2018}}</ref> was a British soldier who, as starting as the [[Evocation|conjurer]] '''Wizardus''' at age 18, was the longest-serving member of the [[The Magic Circle (organisation)|Magic Circle]].<ref name=T/>
Anckorn was born on 10 December 1918 and, at the age of eighteen, became the youngest member of the Magic Circle.<ref name=CM/> During [[World War II]], he served in the [[British Army]], was captured by the Japanese during the [[fall of Singapore]], and forced, as a [[prisoner of war]], to work on the [[Burma Railway]] and the famous [[bridge on the River Kwai]].<ref name=BBC/> He died of bladder cancer on 22 March 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/fergus-anckorn-obituary-kcdc95bd9|title=Fergus Anckorn obituary|author=|date=6 April 2018|publisher=|accessdate=10 April 2018|via=www.thetimes.co.uk}}</ref>
