{{Infobox Podcast |title = ''Sword and Scale'' |image = Sword_and_Scale_Logo.png |caption = |host = [[Mike Boudet]] |language = [[English language|English]] |website = {{URL|http://swordandscale.com}} |updates = Bi-weekly |audio format = [[iTunes]], [[SoundCloud]] |began = January 1, 2014 |ended = |num_episodes = 119 (August 2018) |genre = True crime |cited_for = |cited_as = |provider = Incongruity / [[Wondery]] |num_seasons=5 (June 2018)}}
'''''Sword and Scale''''' is a bi-weekly American [[podcast]] exploring nonfiction stories of [[true crime]]. It features a variety of narrated true crime stories intertwined with interviews with criminals, witnesses, victims, authors, 911 call audio, witness testimony, trial audio, interrogation tapes, music, and sound effects. The podcast was first released on January 1, 2014 by creator, host, Mike Boudet.
Within a year, ''Sword and Scale'' had 1 million downloads and it has ranked in the top 10 of the [[iTunes]] "Science" category, and within the top 5 in the "Social Sciences" category. Popularity increased<ref name="=&quot;RollingStone&quot;">{{cite web |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/lists/beyond-serial-10-true-crime-podcasts-you-need-to-follow-w429955/sword-and-scale-w429957 |title=Beyond 'Serial': 10 True Crime Podcasts You Need to Follow |date=July 22, 2016 |accessdate=July 22, 2016 |work=[[Rolling Stone]]}}</ref> dramatically after the popularity of [[Serial (podcast)|''Serial'']],<ref name="Mash">{{cite web |url=http://mashable.com/2014/11/13/podcasts-detective/ |title=7 podcasts for your inner detective |date=November 3, 2014 |accessdate=November 3, 2014 |work=[[Mashable]]}}</ref> and the show is often compared to it and other podcasts like [[Criminal (podcast)|Criminal]].<ref name="Crim">{{cite web |url=http://podcastpals.net/cast-off-criminal-versus-sword-and-scale/ |title=Cast-Off! Criminal versus Sword and Scale |date=March 28, 2015 |accessdate=March 28, 2015 |work=[[Podcast Pals]]}}</ref><ref name="TbIt">{{cite web |url=http://www.thebolditalic.com/articles/6396-the-best-true-crime-podcasts-that-aren-t-serial- |title=The Best True Crime Podcasts that aren't 'Serial' |date=December 2, 2014 |accessdate=December 2, 2014 |work=[[The Bold Italic]]}}</ref> As of 2016, ''Sword and Scale'' is part of the [[Wondery]] podcast network started by former Fox International Channels CEO Hernan Lopez.
==Controversies== Mike Boudet had allegedly made requests in the past for nude photos from female fans of the podcast, and allegedly sent aggressive tweets to family members who contacted him about using a 911 phone call by a 14-year-old when the 14-year-old's father killed his mother. The call was used in its entirety on the show, with no approval given from the family.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.mamamia.com.au/mike-boudet-sword-and-scale | title=After some revolting comments, people are boycotting one of the most popular podcasts| date=April 6, 2018|work=mamamia.com.au}}</ref>
